PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1781657292
OL,3,CInvest in transport to help Ireland
OL,4,Cwithstand global fuel shocks, says
OL,5,Ccouncil
OL,7,FTransport is Ireland's largest source
OL,8,Fof energy demand, making up 42% of its
OL,9,Fenergy demand and 22% of national
OL,10,Femissions.
OL,12,FIn the transport chapter of its Annual
OL,13,FReview 2026, published on Wednesday,
OL,14,Fthe council said Ireland must reduce
OL,15,Fthe risk of it exceeding its emissions
OL,16,Fceiling by speeding up investment in
OL,17,Fpublic transport, active travel,
OL,18,Felectric vehicle charging
OL,19,Finfrastructure and the grid capacity
OL,20,Fneeded to support cleaner transport.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1781657292
OL,3,CInvest in transport to help Ireland
OL,4,Cwithstand global fuel shocks, says
OL,5,Ccouncil
OL,7,FIt recommended that the Government
OL,8,Fintroduce targeted supports within the
OL,9,Ftransport sector for those most
OL,10,Fexposed and least able to avoid fuel
OL,11,Fcosts, while maintaining planned
OL,12,Fcarbon tax increases and continuing to
OL,13,Fring-fence revenues for climate action.
OL,15,FThe Government announced it would to
OL,16,Fpostpone an increase in the carbon tax
OL,17,Funtil the Budget in October, at a cost
OL,18,Fof 22 million euros, as part of over
OL,19,F750 million euro in supports to help
OL,20,Fwith rising energy costs due to the
OL,21,Fwar in Iran.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
